OFFICE OF DWIGHT D. EISENHOWER
Commodore Hotel
New York, No Y•
October 16, 1952
Dear Mrs. Bixby:
Thank you so much for the amusing
little brass hat ashtray from Paris
which was hand-delivered to my of-
fice on my birthday•
I really
appreciate your thoughtfulness.
I have returned to my office today,
and understand you are on your way
to Tokyo.
I suppose you'll go
through Manila en route -- with more
than a passing thought to the "good
old days."
Those were peaceful
times compared to the present.
Sincerely,
Jupit Diser home.
Mrs. Harold M. Bixby
c/o Mr. Dallas Sherman
AoP•0. 925, Box 323
c/o Postmaster
San Francisco
- 303
